  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6506.72 sitting between the massive negative gamma wall at 6475 (-7.66B) and positive gamma resistance at 6525 (+1.28B), dealers are currently in forced buying mode as they're short gamma and chasing the rally higher. The breakout regime with -5.54B total GEX means dealers will continue amplifying moves - they'll aggressively buy any dip toward 6500/6475 and sell strength into 6525, creating volatile two-way action.\n\nWatch 6525 as the critical inflection point where dealer selling pressure kicks in hard, while any break below 6500 should trigger accelerated dealer buying that could quickly push us back toward the 6515-6525 resistance zone.",
